### 1) **AI Prompt Playground (Local Logic Edition)**

**What it is:**
A sleek web app where users write prompts, tweak sliders (tone, length, creativity), and see how the “prompt” is programmatically transformed and previewed.

**Why it works for the video:**
It _feels_ like an AI product without calling any real AI. You’re showcasing structured thinking: PRD defines inputs/outputs, design sells intelligence, build proves logic. Viewers immediately map it to real tools they use.

**Key features to include:**

- Prompt input textarea
- Control sliders (tone, verbosity, format)
- Real-time “final prompt” output preview
- Preset buttons (YouTube Script, Code Review, Blog Post)
- Copy-to-clipboard interaction

**Estimated demo time:**
~4 minutes
Planning is trivial, UI is flashy, logic is string composition.

