### 5) **Visual Logic Builder (Rules → Outcome App)**

**What it is:**
A drag-ish interface where users define simple rules (“If X and Y → do Z”) and see outcomes update live.

**Why it works for the video:**
This screams “serious engineering” while staying simple. It shows planning → design → logic execution clearly, and the UI movement keeps attention.

**Key features to include:**

- Rule input rows
- Condition toggles or dropdowns
- Live result panel
- Reset / test scenarios
- Smooth transitions

**Estimated demo time:**
~5 minutes
A bit more logic, but visually irresistible.
